aro, Jr.]]\n|[[Kinghaven Farm]]\n|1:42.60\n|-\n|1976\n|[[Bye Bye Paris]]\n|[[Jeffrey Fell]]\n|[[Donnie Walker (horseman)|Donnie Walker]]\n|[[Conn Smythe]]\n|1:43.20\n|-\n|1975\n|[[Deepstar]]\n|[[Lloyd Duffy]]\n|[[David Guitard]]\n|[[Kinghaven Farm]]\n|1:43.20\n|-\n|1974\n|[[Snow Game]]\n|[[Robin Platts]]\n|[[David C. Cross Jr.]]\n|J. F. Hand\n|1:43.80\n|-\n|1973\n|[[Victorianette]]\n|[[Richard Grubb]]\n|[[A. Chris]]\n|S. Asadoorian\n|1:46.60\n|-\n|1972\n|[[Takaring]]\n|[[Avelino Gomez]]\n|[[Arthur H. Warner]]\n|[[Sam-Son Farm]]\n|1:44.00\n|-\n|1971\n|[[Lauries Dancer]]\n|[[Robin Platts]]\n|[[James C. Bentley]]\n|[[Helen G. Stollery]]\n|1:42.80\n|-\n|1970\n|[[Fanfreluche (horse)|Fanfreluche]]\n|[[Chris Rogers (jockey)|Chris Rogers]]\n|[[Yonnie Starr]]\n|[[Jean-Louis Levesque]]\n|1:43.40\n|-\n|1969\n|[[Sno Where]]\n|[[David Dennie]]\n|[[L. Grant]]\n|Green Hills Farm\n|1:43.20\n|-\n|1968\n|[[Hometown News (horse)|Hometown News]]\n|[[Robin Platts]]\n|[[Gil Rowntree]]\n|[[Stafford Farms]]\n|1:44.60\n|-\n|1967\n|[[Lady Taj]]\n|[[Avelino Gomez]]\n|[[Lou Cavalaris, Jr.]]\n|[[George R. Gardiner|G. Gardiner]]/[[Golden West Farms|Golden West]]\n|1:47.60\n|-\n|1966\n|[[Shipmate (horse)|Shipmate]]\n|[[Noel Turcotte]]\n|[[William Thurner]]\n|W. J. Farr\n|1:44.40\n|-\n|1965\n|[[Tie Pilot]]\n|[[Avelino Gomez]]\n|[[William Thurner]]\n|W. J. Farr\n|1:46.20\n|-\n|1964\n|[[Ramblin Road]]\n|[[Avelino Gomez]]\n|[[Gordon M. Huntley|Gordon Huntley]]\n|Gordon F. Hall\n|1:16.80\n|-\n|1963\n|[[Cesca]]\n|[[Jake Burton (jockey)|Jake Burton]]\n|[[H. Hoffman]]\n|[[Stafford Farms]]\n|1:19.20\n|-\n|1962\n|[[Vase (horse)|Vase]]\n|[[Pat Remillard]]\n|[[Robert S. Bateman]]\n|[[Bill Beasley]]\n|1:18.80\n|-\n|1962\n|[[Sun Dan (horse)|Sun Dan]]\n|[[James Fitzsimmons (jockey)|James Fitzsimmons]]\n|[[William Thurner]]\n|W. J. Farr\n|1:18.40\n|-\n|1961\n|[[Glencoe Kid]]\n|[[Al Coy]]\n|[[D. M. Davis]]\n|Mrs. H. Hecht\n|1:18.40\n|-\n|1960\n|[[Hidden Treasure (horse)|Hidden Treasure]]\n|[[Al Coy]]\n|[[John Passero]]\n|[[W. R. Beasley]]\n|1:17.00\n|-\n|1959\n|[[Winning Shot]]\n|[[Avelino Gomez]]\n|[[Richard Townrow]]\n|J. S. Evans\n|1:17.00\n|-\n|1958\n|[[Silver Ship]]\n|[[Ernie Warme]]\n|[[Gordon M. Huntley|Gordon Huntley]]\n|Gordon F. Hall\n|1:20.20\n|-\n|1957\n|[[Pink Velvet (horse)|Pink Velvet]]\n|[[Edward Plesa]]\n|[[John Passero]]\n|[[W. R. Beasley]]\n|1:18.40\n|-\n|1956\n|[[Flying Trapeze (horse)|Flying Trapeze]]\n|[[R. Bureau]]\n|[[E. Howard]]\n|[[Lanson Farm]]\n|1:19.00\n|-\n|1956\n|[[Compactor (horse)|Compactor]]\n|[[T. Johnson]]\n|[[Richard Townrow]]\n|J. Tomlinson\n|1:19.60\n|- \n|1955\n|[[Black Coyote (horse)|Black Coyote]]\n|[[David Stevenson (jockey)|David Stevenson]]\n|[[John Passero]]\n|[[W. R. Beasley]]\n|1:20.00\n|-\n|1954\n|[[Silly Sara]]\n|[[George Walker (jockey)|George Walker]]\n|[[John Passero]]\n|[[W. R. Beasley]]\n|1:18.80\n|-\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n* [http://www.thoroughbredtimes.com/racing-news/2008/June/29/Nicki-Knew-pulls-mild-upset-in-Bison-City.aspx The 2008 Bison City Stakes at ''Thoroughbred Times'']\n\n[[Category:Ungraded stakes races in Canada]]\n[[Category:Flat horse races for three-year-old fillies]]\n[[Category:Recurring sporting events established in 1954]]\n[[Category:Woodbine Racetrack]]\n[[Category:1954 establishments in Ontario]]\n[[Category:Summer events in Canada]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox horseraces\n| class         = Restricted\n| horse race    = Bison City Stakes\n| image         = \n| caption       = \n| location      = [[Woodbine Racetrack]]<br>[[Toronto]], [[Ontario]], Canada\n| inaugurated   = 1954\n| race type     = [[Thoroughbred]] - [[Flat racing]]\n| website       = {{URL|https://web.archive.org/web/20100316214346/http://www.woodbineentertainment.com:80/qct/default.asp}}\n| distance      = {{frac|1|1|16}} miles (8.5 furlongs)\n| surface       = dirt\n| track         = left-handed\n| qualification = Three-year-old fillies\n| weight        = Scale Weight\n| purse         = $191,725 (2016)\n| bonuses       = \n}}\nThe '''Bison City Stakes''' is a [[Thoroughbred horse race]] run annually at [[Woodbine Racetrack]] in [[Toronto]], [[Ontario]], Canada.<ref>[http://www.pedigreequery.com/index.php?search_bar=stakes&query_type=stakes&field=view&id=1485 The Bison City Stakes at Pedigree Query]</ref> Held during first week of July, it is open to Canadian-foaled three-year-old [[filly|fillies]]. Since the 1999  creation of the [[Canadian Triple Tiara of Thoroughbred Racing|Canadian Triple Tiara]], the race has been the second leg of the series.<ref>[https://woodbine.com/woodbine-news/enstone-rocks-in-bison-city-stakes/ Woodbine Entertainment Group, July 9, 2017]</ref> It is contested over a distance of {{frac|1|1|16}} miles on [[Polytrack]] synthetic dirt, the race currently offers a purse of $191,725.\n\nThe Bison City Stakes was first run in 1954 at [[Fort Erie Race Track]] in [[Fort Erie, Ontario]]. Since inception it has been contested at two different distances and at two different venues: \n* {{frac|6|1|2}} furlongs : 1954-1964 at Fort Erie\n* {{frac|1|1|16}} miles : 1965-1976 at Fort Erie, 1977-1979 at [[Woodbine Racetrack]], 1980-2006 at Fort Erie or Woodbine, 2007 to present at Woodbine\n\nIt was run in two divisions in 1956 and 1962. In 1991, [[Francine Villeneuve]] became the first female jockey to win the race. In 2003 there was a [[Tie (draw)|Dead heat]] for first.\n\n==Records==\n'''Speed  record:''' {{small|(Through 1998, Woodbine times were recorded in fifths of a second. Since 1999 they are in hundredths of a second)}}\n* 1:42.15 - [[Awesome Rush]] (2005)\n\n'''Most wins by an owner:'''\n* 7 - [[Sam-Son Farm]] (1972, 1984, 1985, 1987, 1991, 2000, 2003)\n\n'''Most wins by a [[jockey]]:'''\n* 5 - [[Avelino Gomez]] (1959, 1964, 1965, 1967, 1972)\n\n'''Most wins by a [[Horse trainer|trainer]]:'''\n* 4 - [[John Passero]] (1954, 1955, 1957, 1960)\n* 4 - [[James E. Day]] (1984, 1985, 1987, 1991)\n* 4 - [[Roger Attfield]] (1986, 1990, 1993, 2014)\n\n==Winners==\n{| 